1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,160
So you want to become a millionaire

2
00:00:02,160 --> 00:00:04,290
and everyone is telling you to read books

3
00:00:04,290 --> 00:00:06,270
but hardly anyone's got time for that.

4
00:00:06,270 --> 00:00:08,340
Luckily over my many years in business,

5
00:00:08,340 --> 00:00:09,870
I've read hundreds of books,

6
00:00:09,870 --> 00:00:12,150
but there are 40 money making books

7
00:00:12,150 --> 00:00:13,470
that have really stuck with me.

8
00:00:13,470 --> 00:00:16,440
So in this video, I'm gonna
condense all of these books

9
00:00:16,440 --> 00:00:19,980
into the core lessons that
will actually make you rich.

10
00:00:19,980 --> 00:00:21,660
And no, I'm not just saying this,

11
00:00:21,660 --> 00:00:23,370
I have experienced doing it.

12
00:00:23,370 --> 00:00:26,430
I've gone from absolute zero
to making tens of millions

13
00:00:26,430 --> 00:00:28,260
and I didn't make my money on YouTube

14
00:00:28,260 --> 00:00:31,830
like most people on here, I
did it running real businesses.

15
00:00:31,830 --> 00:00:34,410
So I promise that the things
I'm gonna share with you today

16
00:00:34,410 --> 00:00:36,333
will take you from $0 to $100,000,

17
00:00:38,230 --> 00:00:42,570
100,000 to a million, and
a million to $10 million

18
00:00:42,570 --> 00:00:44,370
if you apply them correctly.

19
00:00:44,370 --> 00:00:48,210
Level one, going from zero to $100,000.

20
00:00:48,210 --> 00:00:50,490
First, you need to master your mind.

21
00:00:50,490 --> 00:00:52,410
I didn't come from a wealthy background

22
00:00:52,410 --> 00:00:54,630
and during my youth I vividly remember

23
00:00:54,630 --> 00:00:56,040
people saying the phrase,

24
00:00:56,040 --> 00:00:58,477
money is the root of all evil.

25
00:00:58,477 --> 00:01:02,190
"Secrets of The Millionaire
Mind" explains how these phrases

26
00:01:02,190 --> 00:01:05,430
program us to believe that
rich people are the devil.

27
00:01:05,430 --> 00:01:08,250
It took me a long time to rid
myself of a negative feeling

28
00:01:08,250 --> 00:01:10,980
in my stomach when I
thought about making money.

29
00:01:10,980 --> 00:01:12,570
If I'd have read this book sooner,

30
00:01:12,570 --> 00:01:14,940
it would have helped me
realize this issue earlier.

31
00:01:14,940 --> 00:01:17,760
Once I got over this
hurdle I had to ask myself,

32
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:19,890
what is money actually for?

33
00:01:19,890 --> 00:01:21,967
For me the answer was freedom.

34
00:01:21,967 --> 00:01:24,750
"The Psychology of Money"
puts it a little differently

35
00:01:24,750 --> 00:01:26,340
and says it's all about control.

36
00:01:26,340 --> 00:01:28,320
But I suppose the goal is the same,

37
00:01:28,320 --> 00:01:31,350
to be able to do whatever
you want whenever you want.

38
00:01:31,350 --> 00:01:33,630
It also touches on how
there's a clear difference

39
00:01:33,630 --> 00:01:36,210
between the rich and the wealthy.

40
00:01:36,210 --> 00:01:38,220
Wealth is what you don't see.

41
00:01:38,220 --> 00:01:40,440
The car is not purchased,
diamonds not bought,

42
00:01:40,440 --> 00:01:42,990
renovations postponed, clothes for gone

43
00:01:42,990 --> 00:01:45,000
and first class upgrades declined.

44
00:01:45,000 --> 00:01:48,090
Unfortunately, many
people don't even believe

45
00:01:48,090 --> 00:01:49,860
that they can become wealthy.

46
00:01:49,860 --> 00:01:52,117
I remember my schoolfriend
saying things like,

47
00:01:52,117 --> 00:01:54,990
"I hope I can get an okay
job when I graduate."

48
00:01:54,990 --> 00:01:57,217
They weren't even hoping for a good one.

49
00:01:57,217 --> 00:01:59,760
"The Magic of Thinking
Big" explains that people

50
00:01:59,760 --> 00:02:01,980
