147
00:06:01,230 --> 00:06:04,560
Rather, as they improved their
love for their work grew.

148
00:06:04,560 --> 00:06:06,660
So what skills should you start building

149
00:06:06,660 --> 00:06:08,857
if you aren't necessarily
following your passion?

150
00:06:08,857 --> 00:06:12,030
"The Unfair Advantage"
suggests that to succeed

151
00:06:12,030 --> 00:06:13,650
in an unfair world,

152
00:06:13,650 --> 00:06:15,990
you need to play to
your natural strengths.

153
00:06:15,990 --> 00:06:18,390
Find what you are better
at than most people

154
00:06:18,390 --> 00:06:19,440
and lean into it.

155
00:06:19,440 --> 00:06:22,110
However, it's no longer
enough to just possess

156
00:06:22,110 --> 00:06:24,060
high value skills.

157
00:06:24,060 --> 00:06:28,410
Artificial intelligence is
rapidly replacing many jobs.

158
00:06:28,410 --> 00:06:31,020
I'm using it more and more
in my various businesses

159
00:06:31,020 --> 00:06:32,670
to complete simple tasks.

160
00:06:32,670 --> 00:06:34,890
That's why the idea is shared in "Mastery"

161
00:06:34,890 --> 00:06:36,720
are more important than ever.

162
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:39,090
My main takeaway was
that you need to develop

163
00:06:39,090 --> 00:06:41,910
